.\audits\2026-07-10\evaluation.md:64:The paper still presents harm-blindness as the allocation mechanism, reports +43% delivery and 2.22× against E7, and concludes on the old apparatus (`drafts/paper.md:743-890`, `drafts/paper.md:941-975`, `drafts/paper.md:1264-1299`). It also says allocation and delivery are a layer and safeguard “not two independent effects to be multiplied” (`drafts/paper.md:58-65`), whereas the proposed replacement calls them “two independent layers” (`research/e5-sp-paper-propagation.md:39-51`). The paper claims forty attacks and resolutions through docs/109, while the corpus has 43 through docs/113; the propagation note acknowledges the stale count (`research/e5-sp-paper-propagation.md:80-88`). The v2 design note itself opens with “Not yet implemented” despite the implemented engine (`research/e4e5-value-model-v2.md:3-10`), and the live roadmap still predicts the superseded ~2.8× outcome (`docs/03_ROADMAP.md:38-52`). A demanding reader cannot determine which mechanism, estimand, evidence base, or headline is authoritative.
