.zenodo.json:5:  "description": "Complete research corpus, working paper, and code proposing a functional architecture for distributed public project governance: citizens allocate a mandate-recorded share of an existing public budget across verifiable projects under strict role separation, milestone-gated conditional disbursement, evidential contracts, and role-based reputation — distributed allocation within mandate-bound, visible, versioned, and contestable planning scopes. Includes formal mechanism-design propositions (incentive compatibility of milestone disbursement; collusion-proofness of protocolized fiscalization), a reproducible 10,000-agent simulation of eight experiments (six with pre-registered designs; the one genuinely confirmatory pre-registered test is the later symmetry gate), plus that later pre-registered symmetric selection-only stress test (NO-GO) that retires the earlier compound value-per-budget multiplier as a calibrated effect (the distributed selection advantage is real but small -- a conditional, stylized-model output, not a calibrated real-world effect and not a validated Core v0 implementation; the controlling specification is research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md), and a documented adversarial review record of forty-three attack briefs across five rounds with paired defenses and accepted resolutions, propagated through the architecture corpus for the first four rounds (the manuscript-review round's D037-D040 propagation tracked). The manuscript is drafts/paper.md (Spanish translation drafts/paper.es.md); the accessible companion is docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md.",
README.md:9:> The goal is not to prove that an idea is correct. The goal is to try to destroy it systematically. If it survives, it may deserve to become theory.
README.md:31:Working paper v1.13 (working draft; latest deposited version v1.12, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.21252911) with formal mechanism-design propositions and a reproducible 10,000-agent simulation of eight experiments (six with pre-registered designs — the one genuinely *confirmatory* pre-registered test is the later symmetry gate below). NOTE (2026-07-10): a later pre-registered symmetric, selection-only stress test returned NO-GO and **retires the earlier compound value-per-budget multiplier as a calibrated effect** — the distributed selection advantage is real but small (a conditional, stylized-model output — not a calibrated real-world effect and not a validated Core v0 implementation: pre-registered pooled median ~0.025, below its pre-set 0.05 research-program rebuild gate — not a policy-materiality threshold; a post-hoc ratio-of-sums estimate was ~0.026 [0.023, 0.029]); the earlier agent-based figures are kept only as conditional apparatus outputs. The controlling specification is `research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md`. A complete adversarial record: forty-three attack briefs across five rounds (including a five-profile review of the manuscript itself and a final ablation round), each with a paired defense and an accepted resolution — propagated through the corpus for the first four rounds, with the manuscript-review round's D037–D040 propagation tracked. Current phase: post-manuscript consolidation (publication-readiness remediation; see `audits/2026-07-10/remediation-roadmap.md`). The project's origin distillation is preserved in `knowledge/00_SESSION_2026-06-25_DISTILLATION.md`.
